      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into quarters, then add to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min, then drain (save the pot!) and shake them around the colander to fluff up the edges</p>",
