      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Heat a separate pot over a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>shredded red cabbage</strong>, <strong>sultanas </strong>and <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> to the pot and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook, covered, for 30 min, stirring occasionally – this is your <strong>red cabbage</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
