    {
      "instruction": "<p>Separate your <strong>duck leg[s]</strong> from the <strong>white duck fat</strong> and <strong>duck jelly</strong> (you'll use these in different parts of the recipe!)</p><p>Add the <strong>duck leg[s]</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to the other side of the tray[s] with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>white duck fat</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until everything is golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 4,
