      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved green beans</strong> to the reserved pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>",
